cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.CG 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): The paper deals with the Boolean satisfiability problem (SAT) and threshold programming, which are topics in discrete mathematics. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper discusses the NP-hardness of optimizing temperatures and finding the minimum size TAS, which are both related to computational complexity. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory): The paper uses game-theoretic concepts to analyze the behavior of TASs at high temperatures. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a way to optimize the behavior of TASs, which could be relevant to artificial intelligence applications. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry): The paper deals with the assembly of shapes using TASs, which could be considered a problem in computational geometry.
